Solution:
The area of the shaded region is equal to the area of the square with side length $PQ$ minus the area of the four unshaded right triangles.  The side length of each square is $PQ/4 = 3/2,$ so the area of the square is $(3/2)^2 = 9/4.$

[asy]
for(int i = 0; i < 5; ++i)
