}
}

draw((2,2)--(5,2)--(2,5)--(2,2)--cycle,linewidth(2));

draw((2,2)--(5,2)--(5,5)--(2,5)--cycle,linewidth(1));
draw((2,2)--(5,5),linewidth(1));
draw((2,5)--(5,2),linewidth(1));

label("P",(2,5),N);
label("Q",(5,2),E);
[/asy]

Each right triangle has base and height equal to $PQ/4 = 3/2,$ so each has area $(3/2)^2/2 = 9/8.$  Therefore, the area of the shaded region is
\[\frac{9}{4} - 4 \cdot \frac{9}{8} = \frac{9}{4} - \frac{9}{2} = \boxed{\frac{9}{4}}.\]

